I remember being fascinating with the ridiculous amount of weapons that were available in the game, there must have been at least 50 of them, such as watermelons. You also had the option to attack a wrestler during his entrance, call for interference in the middle of your match, which could bring out a random guy as a friend, or win the women's championship as a dude. The gameplay itself was a whole lot jankier by default, so you could only imagine how difficult it was to do moves with the strange unmappable keyboard controls. The arena was so dark that it felt empty and eerie as well. Weird game in general.
